About this item

  • Ideal Companion for Smart Living Enzriev smart glasses perfectly combine technology and fashion, making your daily life more convenient by easily controlling music and calls, and enjoying the fun that technology brings.
  • Wise Choice for Eye Protection Equipped with blue light filtering lenses, these smart glasses effectively protect your eyes and reduce fatigue caused by prolonged use of electronic devices, making your work and entertainment more comfortable.
  • Ultra-Lightweight Design for Perfect Fit Enzriev smart glasses feature an ultra-lightweight design that feels almost weightless, ensuring comfort during extended wear, allowing you to enjoy music and calls anywhere, anytime.
  • Durable and Suitable for All Activities Made from high-quality TR90 material, these smart glasses are lightweight and also waterproof, dustproof, and sweatproof, making them perfect for outdoor sports and everyday use.
  • Perfect Social Tool Whether at parties, during sports, or leisure time, Enzriev smart glasses allow you to share music with friends, enhancing interaction and making you the highlight of social gatherings.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
4 out of 5 stars
Great Sound Quality!
These Enzriev, Smart Glasses are very cool, I was really surprised by the sound quality when I listened to music from my phone via Bluetooth, it was really good. The glasses are nice and clear, they look great and they don't impair my vision at all. The glasses charged quickly and easily with the included usb charger. The instructions could be a little more indepth to make them easier to maneuver between functions. I did find out after thinking one speaker wasn't working that you need to make sure and turn both sides on because they pair separately. All of the functions seem to work good but as I said, without better instructions, it's not super easy to figure out but doable. I did notice that when I'd attempt to use the voice activation, it also wanted to open my phones Bixby App which was strange, but overall, these are very nice and a decent value.

  • AZdesert35
    3.0 out of 5 stars Interesting but not terribly practical.
    Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2025
    Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    I dont know. Maybe I am just getting old, but a lot of this tech just doesnt excite me anymore. I like the concept and think there is probably some limited market for these, but compared to existing solutions that are much more capable, I just dont know that I see the need for these. The frames are ok if thats the look youre going for, which is why I ordered them. If you want something more modern looking, you might phase out of these sooner than later. The rails feel a little thick for my tastes, but there isnt much you can do if youre trying to build things into them. For me, a nice pair of ear buds will give you better sound and not annoy the people around you. The controls werent too difficult to manipulate. I didnt have issues with how they paired with my device. Like most inexpensive Bluetooth devices, youre not going to get very good range if youre walking around your house or something. I only ran some music through them. I didnt try holding a phone call with someone. I dont really like talking on the phone in the first place. The build quality was good and I think theyll hold up to normal handling. There is a nice soft case, but these should fit in most third-party hard cases you might already have. These are worth a try if you want to test the platform and see if you like that in general. If so, youll probably end up upgrading to something a little more premium. Since you probably cant get Rx lenses in them, if you wear reading glasses or something, these are going to be a hassle to swap back and forth with your regular glasses.

  • Jean-Pierre
    5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent glasses for the price
    Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2025
    Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    There are better smart glasses out there, but if you don't want to spend a lot of money, these are very much worth considering. My first reaction when taking them out was, wow, these look great, very stylish, at least my retro style. They're like gold-tone versions very very similar to my nearsighted glasses, and a good eyeglasses shop should be able to fit them with prescription or polarized lenses. Now, the third and fourth product photos are yet more Chinese Photoshops of the product onto stock photos of face models: the glasses are not quite as big as the photos imply. Ordinarily I'd dock a star or two for that, but the glasses do look as the photos show, with quite nice and sturdy frames, and the size is as the last one shows. They also come with a synthetic leather case (the good kind you press on the end to open) and microfiber cleaning cloth, themselves worth a few bucks at a store.

    I'm not the biggest audiophile, but I found the speaker quality quite quite QUITE decent for this price range. Volume isn't loud loud, but I found it and fidelity very satisfactory. I tested with the "King Arthur" anime soundtrack, the "CHiPs" opening theme, and "Stand By Me" ("Boys Over Flowers" soundtrack).

    Note that the "smart" features aren't built-in but rather activate what is already on your phone, like voice assistant. I was wondering why you'd tap your glasses for camera control instead of just your phone's screen, but then I realized it's something I myself have never done: set up your phone on a distant stand for a group picture you're in, and you wouldn't even need to wear the glasses for the button press.

    The left and right sides are separate, so they power on/off separately and charge with separate cables. This can be handy if you're doing a phone call and want it in just one ear, so that you can hear with the other. The separation makes sense: the top of the frames don't wind up thicker than they are already, and it makes it safer to pop lenses in and out.

  • Woman Veteran
    3.0 out of 5 stars Arms are clunky and the controls are frustrating
    Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2025
    Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    I like bluetooth glasses and wear them in my art classes to listen to music and, if necessary, take calls. I keep them on very low because I don't want to bother others nor do I need them in my business. The sound is decent at low volume, but it gets a bit distorted at higher volumes. My beef is with the arms and controlling the device. It's a great challenge to hit exactly the right spot on either of the arms to turn it off, on, and adjust the volume. I have been using my phone volume buttons because it's such a challenge. Also, these arms are quite thick. They tend to make my ears a bit sore unless I rotate them out with another pair or take them off. The charger is a split Y type cable, with magnets attaching to the inside of each arm. You have to catch the correct arm, as the magnetic chargers aren't interchangeable between the arms. The thickness of the arms adds to the bulk of the glasses, and overall they're functional but not comfortable enough to wear more than an hour or so.

  • TKM
    3.0 out of 5 stars first pair of 'smart' glasses
    Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2025
    Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    I bought these out of curiosity more than anything.

    Pairing to my phone was easy, and once I got used to where the buttons are, they're easy to turn on/off. The mic pics up well enough for phone calls in quiet areas, but in noisier environments, it picks up background noise. If you're spoiled to ANC, you may be disappointed.

    Sound quality is about what you'd expect. Slightly better than if you took earbuds and just held them near your ears without putting them in. Also worth being aware that your audio can be heard by those around you.

    My biggest complaints are:
    1-proprietary charging cable. I avoid products with special cables when possible. These glass were a novelty purchase to try out the concept, so I made an exception, but more cables to keep up with is a negative for me.

    2-They're simply blue-blocking clear lenses, so not sunglasses like advertised.
